The development of the Russian electric car market in addition to the high cost of cars (those electric cars that are sold in Russia, on average twice as expensive as analogues with internal combustion engines) is constrained by the underdevelopment of charging infrastructure (refueling - units), sighs the CEO of "Autostat" Sergey Celikov.
